FBIS4-17294 "drsov078_b_94023" FBIS-SOV-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Foreign Investment Decline in First Quarter Foreign Investment Decline in First Quarter PM2104135394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 21 Apr 94 p I PM2104135394 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN ["Own information" report: "Foreign Investment in Russian Economy Declines in First Quarter" -- from the FINANSOVYYE IZVESTIYA section] [Text] According to preliminary figures from the Russian State Committee for Statistics [Goskomstat], the growth of foreign investment in the Russian economy in the first quarter of 1994 came to $290 million -- a decline of 57 percent on the fourth quarter of 1993. Investments in joint ventures account for around a quarter of all investment. Goskomstat specialists note that this year, as in the past, the quarterly dynamics of foreign investment inflows into Russia are very irregular.
